                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/790: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-25T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 25, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5948. Your 6574, November 21,<note n="30" xml:id="d666fn30">Not printed.</note>
                    indicates that General Hartle has approved the approach to the Irish authorities
                    outlined in the Department’s 5675<note n="31" xml:id="d666fn31">Telegram dated
                        November 12, 10 p.m., <ref target="#pg_769">p. 769</ref>.</note> but does
                    not clearly state your own approval. If you concur in the proposal will you
                    forward the Department’s 5675 to Mr. Gray for the action contemplated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
